    "cooking_instructions": [
        {
            "instruction": "<p><strong>Before you begin...</strong></p><p>Get all your ingredients and equipment ready</p><p>Skim through these steps, then wash your fruit and veg</p><p>Take your <strong>chicken </strong>out of the fridge, open the packet and let it air</p><p>Note: Equipment and pan sizes vary. Make sure you cook food thoroughly (even if it takes you a little longer than 10 min)</p>",
            "order": 1,
            "image": "/images/instructions/creamy-buldak-chicken-thigh-carbonara-noodles/step-1.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p><strong>Now, let's get started!</strong></p><p>Boil a full kettle</p><p>Heat a large, wide-based pan (preferably non-stick) with a drizzle of <strong>vegetable oil </strong>over a high heat</p><p>Once hot, add your<strong> diced chicken </strong>and cook for 9-10 min or until browned all over</p>",
            "order": 2,
            "image": "/images/instructions/creamy-buldak-chicken-thigh-carbonara-noodles/step-2.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Add your <strong>medium egg noodles</strong> to a pot and cover them with <strong>boiled water </strong>until fully submerged</p><p>Bring to the boil over a high heat and cook for 5-6 min or until cooked with a slight bite</p><p>Once done, drain and set aside, reserving a cup of <strong>starchy noodle water</strong></p>",
            "order": 3,
            "image": "/images/instructions/creamy-buldak-chicken-thigh-carbonara-noodles/step-3.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Wash your <strong>spinach</strong> then add to a colander and pour <strong>boiled water</strong> all over it so that it starts to wilt</p><p>Rinse the<strong> wilted spinach</strong> under <strong>cold running water </strong>until it's cool</p><p>Once cool, squeeze as much water out of the spinach as you can</p>",
            "order": 4,
            "image": "/images/instructions/creamy-buldak-chicken-thigh-carbonara-noodles/step-4.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Peel and finely chop (or grate) your <strong>garlic</strong></p><p>Once the chicken has browned, add your <strong>chilli flakes</strong> (can't handle the heat? Go easy!), <strong>chopped garlic </strong>and your <strong>gochujang paste</strong> (not a fan of spice? Just add a little!)</p><p>Cook for 1-2 min or until fragrant and the chicken is cooked through (no pink meat!)</p>",
            "order": 5,
            "image": "/images/instructions/creamy-buldak-chicken-thigh-carbonara-noodles/step-5.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Once fragrant, add your <strong>soft cheese </strong>and <strong>chicken stock mix </strong>to the pan</p><p>Tip: Add a splash of starchy noodle water if your sauce is looking a little dry!</p><p>Add your <strong>drained noodles </strong>and <strong>wilted spinach </strong>and give everything a good mix up \u2013 this is your <strong>creamy buldak chicken carbonara noodles</strong></p>",
            "order": 6,
            "image": "/images/instructions/creamy-buldak-chicken-thigh-carbonara-noodles/step-6.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Grate your <strong>cheddar cheese</strong> finely</p>",
            "order": 7,
            "image": "/images/instructions/creamy-buldak-chicken-thigh-carbonara-noodles/step-7.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Serve the <strong>creamy buldak chicken carbonara noodles</strong></p><p>Top with the <strong>grated cheese</strong></p><p>Enjoy!</p>",
            "order": 8
        }
    ],
